<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,454,1988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">
Cespitose perennials with erect culms. Leaf sheaths hirsute, fibrous and persistent after senescence, leaf blades flat, flexuous, pale, silvery-hirsute. Racemes paired or solitary, 
<quantity box="[999,1110,493,519]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–4 cm</quantity>
long, with rachis narrowly winged, not covering the spikelets. Spikelets paired, subglabrous, lower glumes 5–7-nerved, up to ¾ the length of the spikelets; upper glumes obovate, cucullate, 11-nerved; lower floret usually male, the lower lemma 9-nerved, glume-like; upper floret bisexual.
</paragraph>
